{"action":"closed","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scientific-python/spin/issues/242","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scientific-python/spin","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scientific-python/spin/issues/242/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scientific-python/spin/issues/242/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scientific-python/spin/issues/242/events","html_url":"https://github.com/scientific-python/spin/issues/242","id":2597933823,"node_id":"I_kwDOIIbpT86a2VL_","number":242,"title":"It should be easier to extend commands provided by spin","user":{"login":"ngoldbaum","id":3126246,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxMjYyNDY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3126246?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum","html_url":"https://github.com/ngoldbaum","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ngoldbaum/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2024-10-18T16:21:47Z","updated_at":"2024-11-17T01:20:46Z","closed_at":"2024-11-17T01:20:46Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"NumPy [defines a `spin build` command](https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/dc862b43e3bca09dcf5c235c46b2c7573e2e4b80/.spin/cmds.py#L96), which has fallen out of sync from the upstream `meson.build` command it uses. Reading the click docs, it seems like the pattern NumPy is using with `ctx.forward` is frowned upon.

I think it would be better if spin provided factories for click commands to make it easier for projects to extend upstream commands without having to effectively re-implement their API.

